+## 12. Decision routing — the classifier → SearchDecision handoff (2026-07 fix)
+
+### Symptom
+
+`Who is the new CM of Assam?` · `Who is the principal of DR BKB College?` ·
+`Current Bitcoin price` returned stale model-knowledge answers and **never
+searched**, while `Latest Node.js version` and `Compare Gemini 2.5 Flash vs
+GPT-5` searched correctly.
+
+### Root cause (NOT the wiring)
+
+Every integration point in §9 was already live — chat.js step 5d executes,
+`buildSystemPrompt` injects, the SSE sub-stages stream, `performSearch` fails
+open. The break was **two hops upstream of the orchestrator**, in the
+classify → decide handoff:
+
+```
+user msg ─▶ classifier.js ─▶ toolOrchestrator ─▶ capabilities 'web_search'
+             (classifyTask)     (orchestrate)        └─▶ searchDecision.js
+                  │                                        (decideWebSearch)
+                  ▼                                              ▲
+         ┌──────────────────────┐                               │
+         │ short-message funnel │  msg <55 chars & no            │ taskType
+         │  (defect #1)         │  SUBSTANTIVE signal            │ 'conversation'
+         │  → 'conversation'    │  → forced conversation ────────┘ is a HARD
+         └──────────────────────┘  (simple_qa score discarded)    BLOCK ✗
+```
+
+1. **Classifier short-message funnel** (`classifier.js`): any message under 55
+   chars with no *substantive-task* score was forced to `conversation` — and
+   `simple_qa` is deliberately not "substantive", so a real one-shot question
+   (`Who is the new CM of Assam?`, matching `^who is the`) had its `simple_qa`
+   score thrown away and was relabelled `conversation`. `Current Bitcoin price`
+   matched nothing and was funnelled the same way instead of reaching the
+   zero-score `simple_qa` fallback.
+2. **`conversation` is a hard block** in `searchDecision.js`
+   (`BLOCKED_TASK_TYPES`) — correctly, so `Hey, how are you today?` (which
+   contains the freshness word "today") can't false-positive. But once defect
+   #1 mislabels a factual question as `conversation`, this block guarantees
+   `needed:false` before any signal is scored.
+
+The working cases escaped only because they hit a *substantive* category
+(`Latest Node.js version` → `coding`, `Compare … vs …` → `research`), so the
+funnel never fired.
+
+A secondary gap: even correctly labelled `simple_qa`, the `role_holder`
+positive signal covered only corporate C-suite titles — `CM`, `principal`,
+`governor`, `chancellor`, etc. scored nothing.
+
+### Fix (surgical, integration-preserving)
+
+| File | Change | Nature |
+|---|---|---|
+| `core/classifier.js` | Short-message funnel yields to conversation **only** for greetings/acks and weak sub-threshold chatter; a `simple_qa` signal (or a zero-score message, which the existing fallback routes to `simple_qa`) now falls through instead of being relabelled. Same Simple Question profile, same low-complexity tier — **no profile or budget change**. | tuned heuristic |
+| `search/searchDecision.js` | `role_holder` signal broadened to government / institutional office holders (CM, chief minister, governor, mayor, principal, dean, chancellor, minister, MP/MLA, …) + `who is/are` + `current/new/now` qualifiers. | +coverage, one existing signal |
+| `core/observability.js` | `formatSearchDecisionLog()` — the human-readable `[SEARCH DECISION]` block (Need Search / Reason / Provider / Results / Cache / Tokens Injected / Latency; fail-open variant). Additive; owns no metrics. | additive |
+| `routes/chat.js` | Step 5d emits the decision block on **every** turn (ran *or* skipped), replacing the bare per-branch console logs. | log wiring |
+
+**Deliberately unchanged:** SearchManager, SearchRouter, providers, KeyPool,
+ResultRanker, ContextExtractor, promptBuilder, the capability `override`
+mechanism, and every response shape. The profile still sets the baseline and
+`decideWebSearch` still makes the dynamic call — the fix only stops a factual
+question from being silently reclassified as smalltalk before that call runs.
+
+### Where SearchDecision executes (unchanged, restated for this fix)
+
+`decideWebSearch()` runs inside `orchestrate()`'s capability detection —
+**pure, synchronous, deterministic, before prompt construction**. This fix
+does not move it; it only ensures the `taskType` it receives is honest.
+
+```
+classifyTask ─▶ orchestrate() ┬─▶ capabilities['web_search'].override
+                              │        └─▶ decideWebSearch()  ◀── executes HERE,
+                              │              (no LLM, no I/O)      before any prompt
+                              └─▶ enabled[] ─▶ chat.js 5d ─▶ SearchManager ─▶ prompt ─▶ LLM
+```
+
+### Verification
+
+`npm run test:search-routing` (new, `src/orchestrator/tests/webSearchRouting.js`)
+drives real messages through `classifyTask → orchestrate` and asserts the
+`web_search` capability is enabled for the fresh-knowledge examples and skipped
+for creative / memory / workspace / arithmetic / greeting turns — including the
+load-bearing `Hey, how are you today?` (stays `conversation`) and the demoted
+`clarify … my code` fragment (stays `conversation`, never `research`).
+`npm run test:search` (52/52) and the classifier suite (21/21) confirm the
+decision matrix and classifier contract are intact.
